#X text 114 31 For bpm \, mul and steps \, the number of elements also sets the number of pages and the value for each one. For 'seq' and 'triggers' you set the pitch and trigger toggle values for each step \, and the number of values divided by 16 also sets the number of pages - if you have \, say \, 17 steps \, then you set 2 pages (so the 'ceil' of the division is considered)., f 90;
#X text 583 169 set 3 pages and steps for each;
#X text 466 137 also sets the number of pages to 1;
#X text 530 208 set all picthes (2 pages);
#X text 479 275 If you first set 'bpm'/'mul' and 'step' and then set pitches or triggers expanding to two pages or more \, the same value 'bpm'/'mul' and 'step' values apply to all pages., f 46;
