#X text 952 173 A step sequencer. Left output is MIDI pitch \, 2nd outlet is gate with the duration of half the beat. 3rd is an impulse and rightmost is internal clock., f 37;
#X text 952 252 Pitch values are from 12 to 108 (C0 to C8). At the top of each step you can set note names and octaves directly \, quantized to quarter tones \, but there's support for any interval in MIDIcents. Use number boxes for easier increment in semitones since the knob can't do that \, though it's fun to get random microtones with them. As any knob \, you can type in values but this makes more sense if you do it in the number boxes directly. The toggles set the trigger output on and off for each step., f 37;
#X text 952 463 The left inlet is a gate for running the sequencer \, the mid input is an impulse input for external clock and the right inlet takes an impulse to reset the sequencer to the first step., f 37;
#X text 376 542 You can set many "pages" for different concatenated sequences. Each page has its own BPM \, beat multiplier and number of steps (up to 16)., f 73;
#X text 1024 589 THIS OBJECT IS STILL QUITE EXPERIMENTAL... :), f 18;
